</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B3E819AF0027D973FCD7E3C8FAF90DC5" pageId="1" pageNumber="121" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FB4D4A240027D973FCD7E3C8FC690D51" blockId="1.[810,1452,662,2093]" pageId="1" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="C98696360027D973FCD7E3C8FC5E0BB1" bold="true" box="[863,985,986,1012]" pageId="1" pageNumber="121">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
New species differs from both its congeners in further reduced venation (all veins other than R nebulous or lost, pterostigma reduced up to a colored strip, hind wing with only R preserved and with membrane almost lost basally, and with R not reaching wing midlength) as well as in long, helmet-like head with flat eyes, in smaller size (forewing length under 
<quantity id="3C0AE7C10027D973FA00E4A0FCDD0CB4" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="121" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
), and from 
<taxonomicName id="3CF231A70027D973FC51E4C5FBF40CB5" box="[985,1139,1238,1264]" class="Insecta" family="Serphitidae" genus="Microserphites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soplaensis">
<emphasis id="C98696360027D973FC51E4C5FBF40CB5" box="[985,1139,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="121">M. soplaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also in flagellum much less widened apically.
</paragraph>
